assetProfile.longBusinessSummary: Kyowa Electronic Instruments Co., Ltd. engages in the manufacture and distribution of stress measurement devices in Japan and internationally. It offers various strain gauges; transducers, such as pressure, acceleration, torque, displacement, civil engineering, and automotive transducers, as well as load cells; measuring instruments, including data loggers/analyzers, strain amplifiers/DC amplifiers, and instrument amplifiers. The company also provides measurement systems comprising highway and railroad traffic, automotive test, civil engineering measuring, and test equipment/systems; and software products, such as data analysis, dynamic data acquisition, reading/displaying, control, PCA stress measuring and analyzing, data acquisition/processing, and vehicle safety tests analysis system software. In addition, it offers strain gauges and transducers accessories; connectors, cables, and bridge boxes; and provides measurement consulting, calibration, field, and maintenance contract services. Further, the company manufactures, sells, and exports navigation, surveying, meteorological, and optical instruments, as well as weather equipment. The company markets its products to experimental research fields of government offices, corporations, and universities; national, public, and private universities; automobile; aerospace/ship; railroad; electric, electronic, and precision instruments; general production/machinery; ferrous and nonferrous metals; civil engineering and construction; healthcare/welfare/human engineering; energy; and other industries. Kyowa Electronic Instruments Co. Ltd. was incorporated in 1949 and is headquartered in Tokyo, Japan.
